During my travels i love to capture details and spots on my way. Unforgetable places and epic moments. Sometimes in the simple things we will find the beauty. And as well in moments where you just be on the right second there to catch unique moments is a great feeling too.

Kuala Lumpur is always a great travel destination with lots of good food and historical places and a long history in Asia. A lot of small little streets and as well great monuments from different decades in the history.The British Empire influences mixed with a upcoming modern star in Asia. The Petrona Towers are impressive. Huge aesthetic Monuments in middle of Kula Lumpur. Malaysia i will come back.

Petronas Twin Towers, pair of skyscraper office buildings in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, that are among the world’s tallest buildings. The Twin Towers, built to house the headquarters of Petronas, the national petroleum company of Malaysia, were designed by the Argentine-born American architect Cesar Pelli; they were completed in 1998.
